  <title translate="true">Arguments</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Arguments</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Argument lists are used when calling methods or functions that expect parameters. &#160;There are 2 syntaxes. One that allows named arguments (for the Core dialect when calling functions and methods) and one that does not allow named arguments (used for Properties). The syntax for these argument lists is:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">// NOTE: Separate rule for bracketedarguments because they cannot use idendifierName syntax</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">bracketedArgumentList &#160; </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><tab /><tab /><tab /><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">: unnamedArgument (COMMA unnamedArgument)*</text><br/><tab /><tab /><tab /><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">;</text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">unnamedArgument &#160; &#160;: &#160;expression?</text><br/><tab /><tab /><tab /><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><br/><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">argumentList</text><tab /><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">: &#160;namedArgument (COMMA namedArgument)*</text><br/><tab /><tab /><tab /><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">;</text><br/></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">// NOTE: Expression is optional so we can skip arguments for VO/Vulcan compatibility</text><br/><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">namedArgument</text><tab /><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">: &#160;identifierName ASSIGN_OP &#160;( (REF | OUT) )? expression?</text><br/><tab /><tab /><tab /><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">| &#160;( (REF | OUT) )? expression?</text><br/><tab /><tab /><tab /><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; color:#000000;" translate="true">;</text><br/></para>
